Defendant Enrique Soto in court with attorney Megan L Morrisey.  Defendant Enrique Soto in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the state, the Court orders Counts 2 and 3 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 1.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  3 1/2 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence being served with credit for 124 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment and if necessary complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Take any prescribed medication only in the manner as prescribed by treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with any and all Pick n Save locations within Milwaukee County;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school with part time employment;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program if agent deems appropriate;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $302.34 payable to Pick n Save located at 6760 W. National Ave in West Allis.  Restitution to be paid first and within the first 18 months of probation or any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.   If revoked, the Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.  Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  Appeal rights given. 
Filed;
